        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-10 09:41:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIn principle it is better to have two separate commits for two independent changes, so that the updates can be reviewed in isolation (and potentially reverted without losing unrelated updates).\nIn the comment history it seemed that the line width change was accepted but there was concern about the indentation change. So I split the commit into two different commits for review purposes.",
